name: Decryption Crash Fix
body: This release fixes an important bug that we were seeing in Production where nodes would crash arbitrarily while receiving and decrypting larger payload data

name: Disable Ready Queue Flush functionality
body: This release disables the ready queue functionality since it caused some issues for large data queries.

name: Fix Routing for a few commands in Safe Quorum
body: Minor fixes so the dynomite explorer GUI can work correctly

name: v0.5.7
body:
```
o Bug fixes
o Differentiate before local and remote stats
o Build on Red Hat and CentOS
o Travis test framework
```

name: Stability and Automation Scripts
body:
```
o Efficient Quorum
o Fix Dnode peer mismatch in requests
o Automation scripts
o Florida replacement to provide seeds
o Stability Fixes
```

name: Read and Write Consistency
body:
```
o Consistency facility for reads and writes.
o Support for KEYS, SCAN, HSCAN, inline PING, QUIT.
o Fixes issues with Dnode request response mismatches.
o Support Cluster_describe command on the stats port to get the cluster topology information.
o Reports Redis per operation counters on the stats port.
o -M flag to set the maximum number of allocated messages in the memory.
o Ability to add data stores beyond redis and memcache via the yml file.
  Note: YML files for Dynomite version  <= 0.4 should be updated to a new
  version to have data_store field.
```
